Semi-final matches are slated for Saturday, while the finals will be played on Sunday.There will also be an exhibition match between local team Asec FC and former Kenyan internationals starting from 10am.The former Kenyan internationals will be led by Fred Ambani. Thirty six teams will converge on Mumias Sports Complex in Kakamega County to  compete in the inaugural edition of Barasa Foundation Championship finals starting Friday.
According to the head of the tournament’s secretariat Edward Omung'ala, men and women’s teams will play in pools, with a total of eight matches being played on Friday.



